{comment: Intro}
[G]  [D]  [Em]  [C]

{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[G]Headin' down south to the [D]land of the pines
[Em]Thumbin' my way into [C]North Caroline
[G]Starin' up the road and [D]pray to God I see [C]headlights
[G]Made it down the coast in [D]seventeen hours
[Em]Pickin' me a bouquet of [C]dogwood flowers
[G]And I'm a hopin' for [D]Raleigh, I can [C]see my baby tonight
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_chorus}
[G]So rock me mama like a [D]wagon wheel
[Em]Rock me mama any[C]way you feel
[G]Hey, mama [D]rock me [C]
[G]Rock me mama like the [D]wind and the rain
[Em]Rock me mama like a [C]south-bound train
[G]Hey, mama [D]rock me [C]
{end_of_chorus}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
[G]Runnin' from the cold up [D]in New England
[Em]I was born to be a fid[C]dler in an old-time string band
[G]My baby plays the guitar, [D]I pick a banjo [C]now
[G]Oh, the North country winters keep [D]a-gettin' me down
[Em]Lost my money playin' poker so I [C]had to leave town
[G]But I ain't a-turnin' back to [D]livin' that old life [C]no more
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_chorus}
[G]So rock me mama like a [D]wagon wheel
[Em]Rock me mama any[C]way you feel
[G]Hey, mama [D]rock me [C]
[G]Rock me mama like the [D]wind and the rain
[Em]Rock me mama like a [C]south-bound train
[G]Hey, mama [D]rock me [C]
